## Model flow

Default loop for any non-trivial code change. Run it automatically as part of the normal conversation — never wait for me to trigger an agent by name.

1. Plan: delegate to `planner` (Claude Fable 5 XHigh). It returns an implementation brief: files, approach, constraints, validation.
2. Execute: delegate the brief to `coder` (GPT 5.5 XHigh). Do not write the implementation in the main session.
3. Review: delegate the resulting diff to `reviewer` (Claude Fable 5 XHigh). If it returns corrections, loop coder -> reviewer until accepted. After 3 failed loops, stop and report to me.

Skip the loop for trivial edits (one-liners, typos, config tweaks), pure Q&A, and exploration — handle those directly.

- Use `git` (GPT 5.4 Mini) for status/diff/staging/commit-message chores.
- Pass compact artifacts (briefs, diffs, file lists), not full transcripts.
- The main model orchestrates, keeps context, and gives the final answer.
